@Corazon-jh2rs If you’re not aware of the “exile” the author refers to, those events took place between the 1930s and 1950s. Another genocide called Holodomor in Ukraine happened in 1932–1933 and again in 1946–1947. This isn’t a glimpse twenty years into the future — it’s basic historical knowledge. But since everyone keeps romanticizing russia, why bother acknowledging the facts, right? Do you jump across timelines and randomly drop names because you’re an idiot?

As for the “poor russian girl” who didn’t even live in russia, do you think everyone noticed she’s russian just by chance? There’s a reason for that: her self-identification, her quiet endorsement of her barbaric nation, and her silence, which people tend to mistake for detachment instead of tolerance.

You’re russian, aren’t you? By the way to punctuate it correctly — existence isn’t a crime, unless you’re russian))
